name: Raleigh Jameson
profile_summary: This 30-year-old man is a graduate of the Massachusetts Institute of Technology and works as a Software Developer in the technology industry. He stands 6'1" tall and is originally from Chicago, Illinois, but is currently dating in Los Angeles, California. He speaks English and Spanish and values honesty, ambition, and kindness. His interests include traveling, reading, and hiking. Although he identifies as an agnostic and a liberal, he is looking for a long-term, monogamous relationship. His pronouns are he/him/his and he identifies as straight. He is of white Caucasian ethnicity and does not have any children, though he wishes to have children in the future. At home, he has a dog and a cat. His zodiac sign is Leo and his MBTI personality type is ENTJ. He tends to drink occasionally and does not smoke, use marijuana or other drugs. As for his lifestyle, he believes in an active life and often exercises.
preferences_summary: The user is looking for a long term relationship involving monogamy with a straight woman aged between 25 to 35 years old. The preferred height range of the partner is between 5'4" and 6'0". She should be a non-smoker, may drink occasionally, should not use marijuana or drugs, and have some level of physical activity. The potential partner should also have no children but desire to have them in the future. On the ethnicity front, he is open to dating women of numerous ethnic backgrounds including White Caucasian, East Asian, Black African Descent, Hispanic/Latino, Middle Eastern, Native American, Pacific Islander, South Asian, and Southeast Asian. His potential partner could be moderately involved in politics being either Liberal, Moderate, Conservative, or Not political. The potential match should work in either Healthcare, Technology, Education, Arts, or Finance sectors. Moreover, she should at least speak English and should value Honesty, Kindness, and Ambition. Her interests should include Traveling, Reading, and Fitness, and possess an education level of at least an undergraduate degree.
